sections.Brown-Driver-Briggs:
H109. adab
[אָדַב] verb grieve;
Hiph`il Infinitive לַאֲדִיב (= לְהַאֲדִיב Ges§ 53. 3. R, 7) to cause to grieve 1 Samuel 2:33. (But Dr proposes לְהָדִיב from דוב q. v.)

H119. adom
[אָדֵם אָדֹם,] verb be red (on formation compare LagBN 83 compare 120) —
Qal Perfect3plural אָֽדְמוּ ruddy, of Nazirites Lamentations 4:7;
Pu`al Participle reddened, dyed red, מְאָדָּם Nahum 2:4 (of shield), מְאָדָּמִים of rams' skins Exodus 25:5; 26:14; 35:7, 23; 36:19; 39:34 (all P).
Hithpa`el Imperfect redden, grow or look red, יִתְאַדָּ֑ם Proverbs 23:31 (of wine);
Hiph`il Imperfect emit (show) redness (compare LagBN 120) כַתּוֺלָע יַאְדִּימוּ Isaiah 1:18 (of sins) i.e. be glaring, flagrant (compare also 1:15).

H167. ahal
[אָהַל] verb denominative tent, move tent from place to place (compare Assyrian â'ilu (?) DlW No. 4 & Agl) וַיֶּאֱהַל Genesis 13:12, 18 (J), compare אֹהֶל ישֵׁב (see אֹהֶל);
Pi`el Imperfect יַהֵל (contracted for יְאַהֵל) pitch one's tent like nomad Isaiah 13:20.

H221. Uri
אוּרִי proper name, masculine (fiery, or contracted for אוּרִיָּה)
1 prince of Judah Exodus 31:2; 35:30; 38:22; 1 Chronicles 2:20; 2 Chronicles 1:5;
2 a porter Ezra 10:24;
3 father of an officer of Solomon 1 Kings 4:19.

